               <p>JOHN PORTER. I live with my father, at <placeName id="t18250113-19-crimeloc90">No. 75, in Pall-mall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250113-19-crimeloc90" type="placeName" value="No. 75, in Pall-mall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250113-19-crimeloc90" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250113-19-off88 t18250113-19-crimeloc90"></join>. We lost a book from the shop counter on the 6th of January, about one o'clock. I was not there at the time, but Mrs. Porter raised an alarm, and I followed the prisoner, who had got to No. 99 - I came up with him - it was a Court Guide, quite new. He took it out of his pocket when he came back to the shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250113-19-person172">
                  ABSOLAM 
                  GINN
               <interp inst="t18250113-19-person172" type="surname" value="GINN"></interp>
