                     <interp inst="t18250113-19-person172" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am door-keeper at the exhibition in St. James's-square. I was coming up Pall-mall and saw Mr. Porter running after the prisoner; I caught hold of him, took him back to the shop, and saw him pull the book out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250113-19-person173">
                  EDWARD 
                  JOHN HANDLEY
               <interp inst="t18250113-19-person173" type="surname" value="JOHN HANDLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250113-19-person173" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250113-19-person173" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. He was delivered into my custody; he had no money at all about him; he appears to be a very good scholar - I found some very excellent writing about him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I hope mercy will be extended to me - I did it from necessity, after a long trial for work; I came from Lancashire.</p>
